## Biggest Things I Learned

- Variables are names pointing to objects.
- Functions encapsulate reusable behavior.
- Lists, dictionaries, tuples and sets solve different problems.
- Loops automate repetitive work.
- Functions allow programs to become modular.
- Libraries extend Python without reinventing everything.

